/u/568104?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7","html_url":"https://github.com/canton7","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2016-05-30T09:45:19Z","updated_at":"2016-05-30T09:45:19Z","body":"It's also worth noting that the issue comes and goes across page refreshes, until Syncthing is restarted. \n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/222455443/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"canton7","id":568104,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODEwNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/568104?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7","html_url":"https://github.com/canton7","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/222458117","html_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/issues/3136#issuecomment-222458117","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/3136","id":222458117,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIyMjQ1ODExNw==","user":{"login":"canton7","id":568104,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODEwNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/568104?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7","html_url":"https://github.com/canton7","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2016-05-30T09:59:45Z","updated_at":"2016-05-30T10:07:10Z","body":"Right, part of the issue is that we hit the return at the top of `Serve()` in `gui.go`:\n\n``` go\n    if listener == nil {\n        l.Warnln(\"No listener, so quitting\");\n        // Not much we can do here other than exit quickly. The supervisor\n        // will log an error at some point.\n        return\n    }\n```\n\nGives\n\n```\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:37 WARNING: API: accept tcp 127.0.0.1:8080: use of closed network connection\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:37 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:37 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:37 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:52 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:52 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:52 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:52 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:52 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 10:59:52 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 11:00:07 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 11:00:07 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n[PFQTJ] 11:00:07 WARNING: No listener, so quitting\n```\n\nThat happens because `getListener` fails when it's called from `CommitConfiguration`: listen tcp 127.0.0.1:8080: bind: Only one usage of each socket address (protocol/network address/port) is normally permitted.\n\n... and that happens because the `TCPListener.Close()` docs have the following warning: Already Accepted connections are not closed. Indeed, `TCPListener.Serve()` doesn't return until after we tried and failed to call `getListener`.\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/222458117/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"canton7","id":568104,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODEwNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/568104?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7","html_url":"https://github.com/canton7","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/canton7/orgs","repos_url":"